==English==
===Verb===
'''[[knock]] [[down]]'''
#To [[hit]] or knock (something) so that it [[fall]]s
#:''When I took the can off the shellf, I '''knocked down''' the one beside it.''
#To [[take]] [[apart]] for [[shipping]], [[storage]], or [[demolishion]].
#:''We '''knocked down''' the garden shed when we moved.''
#(at an auction), to [[declare]] [[sold]] with a [[blow]] from the [[gavel]].
#:''The picture was '''knocked down''' for £50.''
#To [[reduce]] the [[price]] of something.
#:''They '''knocked it down''' by another fiver so we bought it.''

